==Polish==
===Pronunciation===
/{{IPAchar|ʒεʧpɔsˈpɔλita}}/
===Noun===
'''rzeczpospolita'''{{f}}
#[[republic]] or [[commonwealth]], nearly always in reference to the official name of the Republic of Poland, ''Rzeczpospolita [[polska|Polska]]'' (abbrev. ''RP''). Other examples: ''Rzeczpospolita Obojga Narodów'' Commonwealth of Poland and Lithuania, ''Polska Rzeczpospolita Ludowa''Polish People's Republic(abbrev. ''PRL'').
# [[w:Rzeczpospolita (newspaper)|Rzeczpospolita]] Daily nationwide newspaper in Poland.

===Declension===
''rzecz-pospolita'' is a [[calque]] translation of the [[Latin]]  ''[[w:res publica|res publica]]'' ("public affair"); hence declines as one word (as adjective) or less often as two words.
